Module Simulator

Package kin.model

This package contains static components of the robot's model.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FixSidePartModel
    Marker interface for components that is in the body direction.
    TailSidePartModel
    Marker interface for components that is counter-body direction.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BodyModel
    A class that represents the robot's body.
    ComponentModel
    An abstract upperclass for any static component.
    ConnectionPointModel
    A ConnectionPoint connects a fix-side-part to a tail-side-part.
    LinearMotorModel
    A Motor that is able to control a certain length in x-direction.
    SegmentModel
    A Segment connects two other parts.
    ServoModel
    A Servo that is able to control a certain angle in the x-y-plane.
    TConnectorModel
    A T-Connector is attached at a fix-side-part and provides two (or more) tail-side-parts.
    TerminationPointModel
    A TerminationPoint is the last component of component chain.
    TouchPointModel
    A TouchPoint is the last component of a component chain and is able to touch the obstacles.
    TouchSegmentModel
    A TouchSegment connects two other parts.
